              "displayName": "Harsh J",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Is there also need for this to be a \"strict\" need or is it good to be flexible (i.e. non guaranteeing) like other resource requests (we do a good locality job to not have this concern very frequently, but still)?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=qwertymaniac",
              "name": "qwertymaniac",
              "key": "qwertymaniac",
              "avatarUrls": {
