          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12617361/comment/13503015",
            "id": "13503015",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bikassaha",
              "name": "bikassaha",
              "key": "bikassaha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845"
              },
              "displayName": "Bikas Saha",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "What is the scenario for this? If it need not be strict then I wonder how its going to be useful. If it needs to be strict then I dont think currently RM strictly supports allocating on a particular node in any guaranteed manner.\nIf debugging is the main scenario then we might be better off using the unmanagedAMLauncher and running the app locally.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bikassaha",
              "name": "bikassaha",
              "key": "bikassaha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845"
              },
              "displayName": "Bikas Saha",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2012-11-23T04:48:20.259+0000",
            "updated": "2012-11-23T04:48:20.259+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12617361/comment/13503137",
            "id": "13503137",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinayakb",
              "name": "vinayakb",
              "key": "vinayakb",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinayak Borkar",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "UnmanagedAMLauncher is good enough for debugging. The reason I am asking for this change is because in our cluster I would like the AM to be launched on a specific host. I am guessing that the strictness guarantee is possibly violated by Yarn when the cluster is fairly busy with other jobs. This is not an issue in my case. I would be using Yarn as a launcher in this cluster for just one application that I would be running.\n\nTo give a little more background, I am trying to port Hyracks (which is an alternate dataflow runtime) to use Yarn as its container launcher. As far as Yarn is concerned, the AM in Hyracks would be a long running job which in turn handles Hyracks Job requests from Hyracks clients. The clusters on which I am planning to run Hyracks using Yarn and where I would like the AM to be scheduled at a specific node, will be dedicated to only running one instance of Hyracks. In this case, I am hoping that the strictness guarantee is met by Yarn.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinayakb",
              "name": "vinayakb",
              "key": "vinayakb",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinayak Borkar",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2012-11-23T10:01:14.952+0000",
            "updated": "2012-11-23T10:01:14.952+0000"
          },
          {
